Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, and business cards, while students utilize tablets at kiosks to upload their resumes to a shared database and sign up for same-day interviews, with a whiteboard displaying interview schedules. An engineering society-sponsored resume review table near the stage offers insights on technical interview preparation, alongside workshops on networking etiquette occurring in an adjoining classroom. The pleasant aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts from the lounge. As the event winds down, monitors display a post-event survey link while staff stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures.

Human resources teams jot notes on tablets as students introduce themselves, while the polished floor is filled with international students seeking visa sponsorship advice and utilizing tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to a shared database. Interview sign-up sheets fill with names as the day progresses, and volunteers stack collapsed booths and collect leftover brochures. Monitors flash a post-event survey link, and the inviting aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts from the lounge, where friends decompress on the quad, discussing their experiences and recruiter engagement. Concurrently, an alumni panel discusses preparation for technical interviews, and career counselors assist students, while some rehearse their elevator pitches quietly against the wall.

Inside, the atmosphere buzzes as students analyze enthusiastic recruiters and compare swag items, including water bottles and phone chargers. Many rehearse their elevator pitches quietly against the wall while clutching resumes in branded folders. Career counselors assist students with maintaining eye contact and guide them toward applicable industries. As the day progresses, interview sign-up sheets fill quickly, and the aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts from the lounge. Volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures as the event concludes. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in an adjoining classroom.

Many students rehearse elevator pitches while clutching resumes in branded folders. Workshops on networking etiquette occur in an adjoining classroom. The pleasant aroma of coffee and catered snacks fills the air near a coffee station, where friends relax and discuss positive responses to their resumes. Monitors display a post-event survey link as volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures.
